Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, the national chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has been asked to step  down as the APC nation Chairman. Oshiomhole was saked to step down by Justice Danlami Senchi on Tuesday pending the determination of the substantive suit seeking his perpetual removal as the APC chairman. Read more: Obasanjo’s commitment to Nigeria remains outstanding  – Buhari More soon